Ivory Coast Coffee-Bean Exports From Abidjan Fell 62% in June

-- B y   O l i v i e r   M o n n i e r
-- 
2011-07-26T17:27:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/ivory-coast-coffee-bean-exports-from-abidjan-fell-62-in-june.html
Exports of coffee beans from  Ivory
Coast ’s port of Abidjan, the commercial capital, fell 62 percent
in June, according to data from the harbor.  Shipments of coffee beans were 4,870 metric tons, compared
with 12,822 tons in the same period a year earlier.  Ivory Coast 
is the  Africa ’s third biggest grower of the beans.  Shipments of soluble coffee, produced in Abidjan, increased
to 660 tons from 543 tons in the same period a year earlier.
Ivory Coast mainly grows the robusta beans, a lower-grade
variety mainly used in instant coffee.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Olivier Monnier in Abidjan via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 